JENKINS CI/CD PIPELINE – MANUAL BUILD

Step 1: Install Java and Jenkins

sudo apt update
sudo apt install openjdk-21-jdk -y

ls
sudo rm jenkins.war
sudo rm -rf ~/.jenkins

wget https://get.jenkins.io/war-stable/latest/jenkins.war

java -jar jenkins.war --httpPort=8087

Open browser:
http://localhost:8087

Unlock Jenkins using:
cat ~/.jenkins/secrets/initialAdminPassword

Step 2: Install ngrok (for webhook connection)

sudo apt update
sudo apt install snapd -y
sudo snap install ngrok

Run ngrok:
ngrok http 8082

Webhook URL format:
http://<ngrok-url>/github-webhook/

Step 3: Create Repository in GitHub

Create a repository and add the following files.

script.sh

#!/bin/bash
echo "Hello from Jenkins Pipeline"

Jenkinsfile

pipeline {
agent any

stages {  

    stage('Clone Repository') {  
        steps {  
            git url: 'https://github.com/username/jenkins-simple-demo.git', branch: 'main'  
        }  
    }  

    stage('Run Script') {  
        steps {  
            sh 'chmod +x script.sh'  
            sh './script.sh'  
        }  
    }  

}  

}

Step 4: Create Pipeline in Jenkins

Open Jenkins Dashboard
Click New Item
Enter project name
Select Pipeline

Pipeline configuration:

Pipeline → Pipeline script from SCM
SCM → Git
Repository URL → GitHub repo link
Branch → main
Script Path → Jenkinsfile

Step 5: Run Build

Click Build Now

Build result:
Green → Success
Red → Failure

Note:
Webhook is used to automatically trigger Jenkins build when code changes occur in the GitHub repository.
